      "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body" : "I have updated the PR with the given suggestions and added the shortcut to most windows.\r\n\r\nThe only one without this shortcut is the 'About Qt' as it is part of Qt and I have not been able to add the shortcut to it.\r\n\r\nIf I have missed any other window please let me know.\r\n\r\n@laanwj `Qt::ApplicationShortcut` does not work for the intended purpose. It makes the shortcut works even if it is not focused.\r\n\r\n\r\n@luke-jr CMD+W is usually only used on macOS, more information can be found in the [macOS HID](https://developer.apple.com/design/human-interface-guidelines/macos/user-interaction/keyboard/) posted by @jonasschnelli and in [Wikepedia's Table of keyboard shortcuts](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Table_of_keyboard_shortcuts).\r\n",
      "created_at" : "2019-04-19T10:26:19Z",
